        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 5:14PM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL</headline>
        <description>At 513 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 13 miles southwest of Sebring to 11 miles
northeast of Arcadia to near Arcadia. Movement was northwest at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Arcadia, Ona, Zolfo Springs, Wauchula, Limestone, Gardner,
Brownville, and Sweetwater.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
